line_1: Dispute those Terms for which so long they su'd,
line_2: To see th' Audacious Foe, so late subdu'd,

line_1: To whom proud Oriel and Azuriel su'd,
line_2: She, whom at distance thrones and princedoms view'd,

line_1: And for the glorious prize to Simma su'd;
line_2: With ravish'd eyes her heav'nly face he view'd,

line_1: When to the gouty alderman I sued,
line_2: The nasty fellow, ('gad!) was downright rude.

line_1: Low at her feet full many a prince had sued,
line_2: But all their blandishments her heart withstood;

line_1: No gallant youth my presence su'd,
line_2: An easy passage through the crowd
